Morningstar ETJ commentary:

"While we are intrigued by this fund's strategy that includes protective put
options, that strategy has restrained the fund's long-term performance. We also
do not like this fund's level distribution plan, which relies heavily on return
of capital. While the covered call strategy can cause a fund to use more return
of capital than a similar fund not using a call overlay, this fund has used it
destructively in the past two fiscal years with little sign of relief. Its
level distribution plan only adds to the pain, and, not surprisingly, the
distribution was lowered from $0.45 per share each quarter to $0.3195 in
December 2010."

That makes ETJ an avoid for me.
